rComments: Katherine is easily one of my favourite professors at UTSC. Her insight and knowledge blends into her own research. She is also passionate about what she teaches and it really shows by not being afraid to speak her own mind on certain matters, and relating it to contemporary world issues. I look forward to having more courses with her at the helm.
LOVED HER. great with her lectures, questions, and marking. one of my faves at uoft

Professor Blouin is so helpful and very passionate!! I took this course as a program requirement and ended up really liking it! She got the class motivated. She was very approachable for questions/answers, she helped me ace my paper and bring my mark up (from almost failing the midterm). Make sure you do the readings and go to class!

This prof is great, she is always willing to help via email or in person. Hated the formats of her exams they were all over the place but gave lots of opportunity to earn marks elsewhere, essay worth 20% and short assignment worth 10%. She posts lecture notes via intranet. She is young, spunky and HOT!

Very intelligent, open-minded and passionate professor, I admire her continuous devotion to her field of research, she's very helpful with her students, available for them. She's very well prepared in class. The kind of person who will change your life for the best and motivate you to achieve your goals. Long life to Dr. Katherine Blouin.
Really enthusiastic, makes class a lot of fun. Not too difficult if you pay attention and work hard
Midterm and final exam s are simple, if you go to class and pay attention you should be fine.
Final Essay very difficult and too many sources needed to do properly. Unhelpful with comments. Tests are moderatley fair, reading material too much.
